page.title: 09Animal Life
page.content: In Penshurst there are cats, dogs, rabbits, gerbils, foxes, fish, birds including owls geese swans and herons, farm animals, wasps and bees, frogs, toads, newts and grass snakes to mention just a few. The game keeper said that he looks after labradors, they cost Â£3 a week to feed. He also looks after 2,000 pheasants each year. The pheasants are reared for Lord De L'Isle's shoots. Some survive and are seen all over our area. The game keeper sees deer, woodpeckers, cuckoos and nightingales. He also sees about 6 poachers who seem to be very active from October to February.
